@page "/learn/getting-started"
@layout MacroSutra.Web.Components.Layout.LandingLayout

<PageTitle>MacroSutra - Getting Started</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-section">
    <div class="landing-container">
        <h1>Getting Started with MacroSutra</h1>
        <p>This guide walks you through creating an account, linking a brokerage, building your first strategy, and monitoring your portfolio.</p>

        <h2 id="account">1. Create Your Account</h2>
        <p>MacroSutra uses DAISI single sign-on (SSO) for authentication. If you already have a Daisinet account, you can log in immediately. Otherwise, create a free account:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Click <strong>Create Account</strong> in the top navigation.</li>
            <li>Complete the registration form on the DAISI SSO page.</li>
            <li>After registration, you'll be redirected back to MacroSutra and automatically signed in.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>The first user on an account is automatically assigned the <strong>Owner</strong> role with full permissions.</p>

        <h2 id="brokerage" class="mt-4">2. Link a Brokerage Account</h2>
        <p>Connect your brokerage to trade and track positions through MacroSutra:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Portfolio &rarr; Brokerage Accounts</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Link Account</strong> and select your broker.</li>
            <li>Enter your API credentials (see provider-specific instructions below).</li>
            <li>MacroSutra validates your credentials before saving.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Sync Now</strong> to fetch your positions and balance.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You can connect multiple accounts from different brokers. All positions are aggregated into a single portfolio view.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Supported Brokerages</h3>

        <h4>Paper Trading</h4>
        <p>No credentials required. Use Paper accounts for testing strategies without risking real capital. Paper accounts return mock data with a $100,000 starting balance.</p>

        <h4>Alpaca</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Create an account at <a href="https://app.alpaca.markets" target="_blank">app.alpaca.markets</a>.</li>
            <li>Go to your dashboard and generate an <strong>API Key</strong> and <strong>Secret Key</strong>.</li>
            <li>In MacroSutra, select <strong>Alpaca</strong> as the provider and enter your keys.</li>
            <li>Toggle <strong>Paper Trading</strong> on to use Alpaca's sandbox environment, or leave it off for live trading.</li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Webull</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Apply for API access at <a href="https://www.webull.com/open-api" target="_blank">developer.webull.com</a>.</li>
            <li>Create an app and obtain your <strong>App Key</strong> and <strong>App Secret</strong>.</li>
            <li>Generate an <strong>Access Token</strong> and optional <strong>Refresh Token</strong> via the OAuth flow.</li>
            <li>In MacroSutra, select <strong>Webull</strong> as the provider and enter all credentials.</li>
            <li>Toggle <strong>Sandbox Mode</strong> on to use Webull's test environment.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Webull tokens expire periodically. MacroSutra automatically refreshes tokens using your refresh token when syncing.</p>

        <h2 id="strategies" class="mt-4">3. Create Your First Strategy</h2>
        <p>Strategies in MacroSutra are built from three components:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Triggers</strong> — Events that start evaluation (e.g., price crosses a threshold, technical indicator signal, scheduled time).</li>
            <li><strong>Conditions</strong> — Rules that must be true for the strategy to act (e.g., position size limits, time-of-day window, portfolio allocation cap).</li>
            <li><strong>Actions</strong> — What happens when triggers fire and conditions pass (e.g., buy/sell shares, send a notification, adjust a position).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To create a strategy:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Strategies</strong> in the sidebar and click <strong>New Strategy</strong>.</li>
            <li>Give your strategy a name and optional description.</li>
            <li>Add one or more <strong>triggers</strong> — select a trigger type and configure its parameters.</li>
            <li>Add <strong>conditions</strong> to filter when the strategy should execute.</li>
            <li>Define <strong>actions</strong> to specify what trades or notifications to perform.</li>
            <li>Choose a target brokerage account for trade execution.</li>
            <li>Save the strategy. You can activate it immediately or test with paper trading first.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="execution" class="mt-4">How Strategies Execute</h2>
        <p>Once a strategy is activated, MacroSutra's evaluation engine automatically monitors and executes it:</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Evaluation Cycle</h3>
        <p>A background service runs every <strong>60 seconds</strong> during US market hours (<strong>9:30 AM – 4:00 PM Eastern</strong>, Monday through Friday). Each cycle:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Fetches live market data (price, volume, daily change) for all symbols across active strategies.</li>
            <li>Retrieves historical price data for technical indicator calculations (SMA, EMA, RSI, MACD).</li>
            <li>Evaluates each strategy's trigger conditions against the current data.</li>
            <li>If all conditions pass (AND mode) or any condition passes (OR mode), executes the strategy's actions.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Market data is cached for 30 seconds to avoid redundant API calls when multiple strategies share the same symbols.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Condition Types</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Price</strong> — Current market price of the symbol.</li>
            <li><strong>Volume</strong> — Daily trading volume.</li>
            <li><strong>Percent Change</strong> — Daily price change as a percentage.</li>
            <li><strong>Moving Average (SMA)</strong> — Simple moving average over a configurable period.</li>
            <li><strong>RSI</strong> — Relative Strength Index (0–100) over a configurable period. Default 14.</li>
            <li><strong>MACD</strong> — MACD line value (fast EMA – slow EMA). Default 12/26/9.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Operators</h3>
        <p>Each condition compares the current value to a target using one of these operators:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Greater Than / Less Than</strong> — Standard comparison.</li>
            <li><strong>Greater Than or Equal / Less Than or Equal</strong> — Inclusive comparison.</li>
            <li><strong>Equal</strong> — Exact match.</li>
            <li><strong>Crosses Above</strong> — Triggers when the value moves from below to above the target.</li>
            <li><strong>Crosses Below</strong> — Triggers when the value moves from above to below the target.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><em>Note: CrossesAbove/CrossesBelow use in-memory tracking, so a server restart resets the crossing detection. The first evaluation after restart will not detect a crossing.</em></p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Quantity Resolution</h3>
        <p>When a trade action fires, the quantity is resolved based on the sizing mode:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Shares</strong> — Trade the exact number of shares specified.</li>
            <li><strong>Dollar Amount</strong> — Divide the dollar amount by the current price to calculate shares.</li>
            <li><strong>Percent of Portfolio</strong> — Calculate shares based on a percentage of your account balance.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Testing Strategies</h3>
        <p>Before activating a strategy, use the <strong>Test Now</strong> button on the Strategies page or the <strong>Test Conditions</strong> button in the strategy editor. This evaluates your conditions against live market data and shows per-condition pass/fail results without placing any trades.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Order Tracking</h3>
        <p>After an order is placed, a separate tracker checks order status every 30 seconds and updates the trade record when orders are filled, partially filled, cancelled, or rejected.</p>

        <h2 id="backtesting" class="mt-4">4. Backtesting Your Strategies</h2>
        <p>Before risking real capital, test your strategies against historical market data to see how they would have performed.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Running a Backtest</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Trading &rarr; Backtesting</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>New Backtest</strong>.</li>
            <li>Select a strategy from your saved strategies.</li>
            <li>Enter a stock symbol (e.g., <strong>AAPL</strong>).</li>
            <li>Choose a start date and end date for the simulation period.</li>
            <li>Set your initial capital (default $100,000).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Run Backtest</strong>. The engine will simulate your strategy against historical daily bars.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Understanding Results</h3>
        <p>After a backtest completes, you'll see:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Performance metrics</strong> — Total return, Sharpe ratio, max drawdown, win rate, profit factor, total trades, and per-trade averages.</li>
            <li><strong>Equity curve</strong> — A line chart showing how your portfolio value changed over time.</li>
            <li><strong>Drawdown chart</strong> — Shows the peak-to-trough decline at each point, helping you understand risk.</li>
            <li><strong>Trade table</strong> — Every simulated trade with entry/exit prices, P&amp;L, return percentage, and duration.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Key Metrics Explained</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Total Return %</strong> — Overall percentage gain or loss from initial capital.</li>
            <li><strong>Sharpe Ratio</strong> — Risk-adjusted return. Higher is better; above 1.0 is generally considered good.</li>
            <li><strong>Max Drawdown %</strong> — The largest peak-to-trough decline. Shows worst-case loss from a high point.</li>
            <li><strong>Win Rate</strong> — Percentage of trades that were profitable.</li>
            <li><strong>Profit Factor</strong> — Gross profits divided by gross losses. Above 1.0 means the strategy is profitable overall.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Limitations</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Backtests use <strong>daily bars only</strong> — intraday price movements are not simulated.</li>
            <li>No slippage or commission modeling — actual results may differ slightly due to execution costs.</li>
            <li>Trades execute at the daily close price, which may not reflect real-world fill prices.</li>
            <li>Single symbol per backtest — multi-symbol strategies are evaluated against one symbol at a time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="sharing" class="mt-4">5. Sharing Your Strategies</h2>
        <p>MacroSutra has a built-in strategy marketplace where you can share your strategies with the community and discover strategies from other traders.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Making a Strategy Public</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Open a strategy in the strategy editor.</li>
            <li>Change the <strong>Visibility</strong> dropdown from <strong>Private</strong> to <strong>Public</strong>.</li>
            <li>Save the strategy. It will now appear in the <a href="/marketplace">Strategy Marketplace</a>.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You can also set visibility to <strong>Subscribers Only</strong> to share with your subscribers but not the general public.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Browsing the Marketplace</h3>
        <p>Visit the <a href="/marketplace">Marketplace</a> to browse public strategies shared by the community. You can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Sort strategies by newest or name.</li>
            <li>View strategy details including conditions, actions, and community stats.</li>
            <li>See ratings and reviews from other users.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Forking a Strategy</h3>
        <p>Found a strategy you like? <strong>Fork it</strong> to create your own copy that you can customize:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Open any public strategy from the marketplace.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Fork</strong> — this creates a private copy in your account.</li>
            <li>The forked strategy starts as inactive. Modify conditions, actions, or symbols as needed.</li>
            <li>Activate it when ready. The fork maintains attribution to the original author.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Ratings and Reviews</h3>
        <p>Help the community by rating and reviewing strategies you've tried:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Rate strategies from 1 to 5 stars.</li>
            <li>Add an optional text review explaining your experience.</li>
            <li>You can leave one review per strategy. Edit or delete it at any time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Strategy Leaderboard</h3>
        <p>The <a href="/leaderboard">Leaderboard</a> ranks public strategies by backtested performance. Sort by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Sharpe Ratio</strong> — Risk-adjusted return (higher is better).</li>
            <li><strong>Total Return</strong> — Raw percentage gain.</li>
            <li><strong>Win Rate</strong> — Percentage of profitable trades.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Only strategies with completed backtests appear on the leaderboard. Run backtests on your public strategies to get ranked!</p>

        <h2 id="subscriptions" class="mt-4">6. Subscribing to Strategies</h2>
        <p>Subscribe to other traders' strategies to automatically receive trade signals when their strategies fire.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">How to Subscribe</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Browse the <a href="/marketplace">Strategy Marketplace</a> and find a strategy you want to follow.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Subscribe</strong> on the strategy detail page.</li>
            <li>Choose an action type:</li>
        </ol>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Mirror</strong> — Automatically execute the same trade on your connected brokerage account.</li>
            <li><strong>Scaled Mirror</strong> — Mirror trades with a custom scale factor (e.g., 0.5x = half the quantity).</li>
            <li><strong>Email Alert</strong> — Receive an email with trade details when the strategy fires.</li>
            <li><strong>Webhook</strong> — POST trade data to your custom URL for external integrations.</li>
        </ul>
        <ol start="4">
            <li>Configure the required fields (brokerage account for mirror, email for alerts, URL for webhooks).</li>
            <li>If the strategy has a credit price, credits are deducted from your Daisinet balance.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Subscribe</strong> to confirm.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Managing Subscriptions</h3>
        <p>Visit <strong>Subscriptions</strong> in the sidebar to see your active subscriptions. You can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>View action history — see every trade signal received and whether it succeeded.</li>
            <li>Cancel a subscription at any time.</li>
            <li>Switch to the <strong>My Subscribers</strong> tab to see who's subscribed to your strategies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-3">Publishing Strategies for Subscribers</h3>
        <p>To accept subscribers, set your strategy's visibility to <strong>Public</strong> or <strong>Subscribers Only</strong>, then optionally set a credit price and billing period in the strategy editor.</p>

        <h2 id="portfolio" class="mt-4">7. View Positions and Trades</h2>
        <p>Once your brokerage is linked and strategies are running:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dashboard</strong> — Overview of portfolio value, recent trades, and active strategies.</li>
            <li><strong>Positions</strong> — Current holdings with real-time P&amp;L across all accounts.</li>
            <li><strong>Trades</strong> — Full trade history with filtering by strategy, symbol, and date range.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="team" class="mt-4">8. Team Management</h2>
        <p>MacroSutra supports team accounts imported from your Daisinet organization:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings &rarr; Team</strong>.</li>
            <li>Team members from your Daisinet account can be activated for MacroSutra access.</li>
            <li>Assign roles: <strong>Viewer</strong> (read-only), <strong>Trader</strong> (can execute), <strong>Admin</strong> (full management), or <strong>Owner</strong> (account owner).</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="mt-4"><a href="/learn">← Back to Learn</a></p>
    </div>
</section>
